msgctxt "Description"
msgid ""
"You can get the list of available quotes from <a href=\"https://boursorama."
"com/bourse/\">Boursorama</a>.<br/>Then, enter the symbol of the expected "
"quotes."
msgstr ""
"You can get the list of available quotes from <a href=\"https://boursorama."
"com/bourse/\">Boursorama</a>.<br/>Then, enter the symbol of the expected "
"quotes."

#: skgbankmodeler/sources/org.kde.skrooge-source-coinmarketcap.json
msgctxt "Description"
msgid ""
"You can get the list of available quotes from <a href=\"https://"
"coinmarketcap.com\">CoinMarketCap</a>.<br/><br/>Then, you must create an "
"account to get an API key and set it in setting.<br/>Then, enter the "
"expected quote in expected currency. Example: if you want BTC in USD, you "
"must enter BTC-USD."
msgstr ""
"You can get the list of available quotes from <a href=\"https://"
"coinmarketcap.com\">CoinMarketCap</a>.<br/><br/>Then, you must create an "
"account to get an API key and set it in setting.<br/>Then, enter the "
"expected quote in expected currency. Example: if you want BTC in USD, you "
"must enter BTC-USD."

#: skgbankmodeler/sources/org.kde.skrooge-source-cryptocompare.json
msgctxt "Description"
msgid ""
"You can get the list of available quotes from <a href=\"https://www."
"cryptocompare.com/\">CryptoCompare</a>.<br/>Then, you must create an account "
"to get an API key and set it in setting.<br/>Then, enter the <expected "
"quote>-<in the expected currency>. Example: if you want BTC in USD, you must "
"enter BTC-USD."
msgstr ""
"You can get the list of available quotes from <a href=\"https://www."
"cryptocompare.com/\">CryptoCompare</a>.<br/>Then, you must create an account "
"to get an API key and set it in setting.<br/>Then, enter the <expected "
"quote>-<in the expected currency>. Example: if you want BTC in USD, you must "
"enter BTC-USD."

